Code in Motion (CiM) Maintainers
==================================

This file provides information about the maintainers of the Code in Motion
project. Maintainers are responsible for reviewing patches, managing releases,
and ensuring the project's overall health and direction.

Patch Submission
----------------
All patches should follow the guidelines in CONTRIBUTING.md and must include
a Signed-off-by line as per the Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO).

See also:
- CONTRIBUTING.md for detailed contribution guidelines
- DCO for the Developer Certificate of Origin
- CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md for community standards

Maintainer Responsibilities
---------------------------
Maintainers are expected to:
- Review and merge pull requests in a timely manner
- Maintain code quality and project standards
- Respond to issues and community questions
- Coordinate releases and version management
- Ensure security issues are addressed promptly
- Guide the technical direction of the project

How to Become a Maintainer
--------------------------
Contributors who demonstrate sustained commitment to the project through
high-quality contributions, code reviews, and community engagement may be
invited to become maintainers.

Format
------
The following format is used for each maintainer entry:

M: Maintainer name <email@address>
R: Designated reviewer (optional)
L: Mailing list (if applicable)
S: Status (Supported, Maintained, Odd Fixes, Orphan, Obsolete)
F: File or directory pattern

Status meanings:
    Supported:     Someone is actually paid to look after this
    Maintained:    Someone actually looks after it
    Odd Fixes:     It has a maintainer but they don't have time to do
                   much other than throw the odd patch in
    Orphan:        No current maintainer, needs a new one
    Obsolete:      Old code, should be replaced or removed

